SIMPLE: infliction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infliction
<hw>In*flic"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inflictio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infliction</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of inflicting or imposing; <as>as, the <ex>infliction</ex>
of torment, or of punishment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is inflicted or imposed, as punishment,
disgrace, calamity, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His severest <qex>inflictions</qex> are in themselves acts of
justice and righteousness.</q> <rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflictive</ent>⟦br⟧
